OL,5, Repeated human errors made for years   
OL,6, were to blame for a scandal which led  
OL,7, to more than #1bn of state pensions not
OL,8, being paid, a report has concluded.    
OL,10,FThe National Audit Office (NAO) said   
OL,11,F134,000 pensioners, mostly women, were 
OL,12,Funderpaid pensions because outdated    
OL,13,Fcomputer systems led to mistakes.      
OL,15,FAmong them was 74-year-old Irene Wise, 
OL,16,Fwho said women like her were           
OL,17,F"short-changed" for years.             
OL,19,FThe government said everyone would     
OL,20,Freceive what they were owed.           
